Author: siu - Chainmakers#3920
Content: in this breakthrough places its better to look at higher timeframes

Author: siu - Chainmakers#3920
Content: then it makes more sense to see where the consolidations should happen.

Author: siu - Chainmakers#3920
Content: https://cryptocharts.org/i/1550578403.png

Author: siu - Chainmakers#3920
Content: for example this daily chart presents a very bullish picture but the 200sma will take longer to curve up and become the floor for further prices rise.

Author: siu - Chainmakers#3920
Content: So it will make sense for the price to consolidate for a bit more until we get longer period moving averages to curve

Author: siu - Chainmakers#3920
Content: https://cryptocharts.org/i/1550578518.png

Author: siu - Chainmakers#3920
Content: On the weekly scale , if you take volume as a sole indicator, the picture is overall bullish but it does seem like it will not be so easy to break above 41ema without a longer fight.

Author: siu - Chainmakers#3920
Content: imo, now a range consolidation around these levels makes sense

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: what? the price wont double everyday forever?

Author: siu - Chainmakers#3920
Content: Also it would make a lot of sense to build a strong support at $1 so that it becomes a long term floor

Author: siu - Chainmakers#3920
Content: If we really want to see KMD shinning we will take a couple of years on rise/consolidate/rise/consolidate pattern.

Author: siu - Chainmakers#3920
Content: and on the first waves of a bull market, the rises tend to be smaller and the consolidations longer

Author: siu - Chainmakers#3920
Content: then after the realization of full bull market sets in, the pattern is for more extreme rises and more deep and short period corrections.

Author: siu - Chainmakers#3920
Content: the first corrections are sideways, flat, slow and boring, since the motive is uncertaint and accumulation

Author: siu - Chainmakers#3920
Content: the corrections later on a bull trend are deep and fast because the motivations are profit taking and fear of topping.
